id=3D\"breadcrumbs\">=0D=0A                        <!-- Breadcrum=\r\nb NavXT 4.1.0 -->=0A<span id=3D\"bstart\" style=3D\"color:#666666;font-weight:=\r\nbold;\">You are here:</span> <a <p>Having sp=\r\nent his youth and early adult years playing sports and working out religiou=\r\nsly, Adam experienced the pros and cons of many workout programs. His educa=\r\ntional pursuits were focused on Biology and other sciences. Adam wanted to =\r\nknow and experience his own Biology and push himself to his limits.</p>=0A<=\r\np>So it came as no surprise that after discovering the amazing results from=\r\n a slow motion fitness system that he dug in deeper and ultimately, Adam Zi=\r\nckerman has made his career teaching people how to get more fit in less tim=\r\ne than they ever thought possible. Starting out in a Long Island basement t=\r\ninkering and refining both equipment and technique, InForm Fitness was born=\r\n.</p>=0A<p>Today, Adam is the founder and owner of the InForm Fitness Studi=\r\nos where he and his specially trained team deliver the Power of 10 program =\r\nthat inspired this book. Adam has appeared on numerous television shows, as=\r\n well as in feature stories in national magazines. His <em>Power of 10 </em=\r\n>clients include media celebrities, athletes, doctors, business professiona=\r\nls, moms, and office workers =E2=80=93 all of whom share the desire to get =\r\nand stay in shape for healthier, happier lives.</p>=0A<p><strong>Read the B=\r\nook!</strong></p>=0A<p><em>Power of 10</em> is the revolutionary slow motio=\r\nn fitness system that will transform your body and the way you think about =\r\nexercise, rest, and nutrition forever. Imagine a fitness program so powerfu=\r\nlly effective, you can:</p>=0A<ul>=0A<li>Work out 20 to 25 minutes, once a =\r\nweek, for maximum strength, fat loss, and fitness</li>=0A<li>Follow a nutri=\r\ntion plan that doesn=E2=80=99t permit hunger</li>=0A<li>Rest your way to su=\r\nccess</li>=0A<li>Eliminate painful injuries, no matter what your age or exp=\r\nerience</li>=0A<li>Finally begin a program that even the busiest, most stre=\r\nssed-out person can follow with hardly a break in schedule or change in rou=\r\ntine</li>=0A</ul>=0A<p>&nbsp;</p>=0A\t\t\t\t   =0D=0A Adam&#8217;s program works. -<strong>-L=\r\neslie Stahl</strong></p></blockquote>=0A<h6><strong></strong>The following =\r\nis an excerpt from Adam&#8217;s book, <span style=3D\"text-decoration: under=\r\nline;\">The Power of 10</span>:</h6>=0A<p>Here is the secret I found. Because no fitness program, mo matter how great, can possibly work i=\r\nf you DON&#8217;T DO IT. I know how many exercise programs I&#8217;ve quit =\r\nin my life after 3 weeks. What about you? Just imagine where you&#8217;ll b=\r\ne 3, 6, 12 months and years from now when you&#8217;ve got a world-class fi=\r\ntness program that you actually stick with? That you actually look forward =\r\nto after 5-7 days off? You&#8217;ll be in buff-land, that&#8217;s where you=\r\n&#8217;ll be. And you&#8217;ll never want to go back.</p>=0A<p>THE 1-2-3 OF=\r\n POWER OF 10</p>=0A<p><em>Power of 10</em> is made up of three parts I call=\r\n &#8220;The Three Pillars,&#8221; which together make it a program for tota=\r\nl body health and fitness. Believe it or not, it&#8217;s during rest that all the=\r\n positive changes happen. By its very nature and design,<em> Power of 10</e=\r\nm>, more than any other regimen, &#8220;positions&#8221; your body to get t=\r\nhe rest and recovery it needs.</p>=0A<p>&nbsp;</p>=0A<p><a             <h2>Wondering If The <em>Power of 10</em> Work=\r\nout Is For You?</h2>=0A<p>While we believe that anyone, at any age can and =\r\nshould do the <em>Power of 10</em> regime, we recognize shouldn&#8217;t work out &#8211; we say <em><strong>Nonsense</strong></e=\r\nm>!</p>=0A<p>We do recommend that if you are pregnant or suffering from an =\r\naliment that you check with your doctor first. Once you&#8217;ve gotten the=\r\n thumbs up, then stop in for a free consultation. We&#8217;ve been having g=\r\nreat success with young adults in their 20&#8242;s, seniors into their 90&#=\r\n8242;s, and every age in between.=C2=A0 Our clients range in their overall =\r\ncondition, each achieving success. Yes, we weren&#8217;t exaggerating we ha=\r\nve clients in their 90&#8242;s! Better than relating however, is resolving. And InForm Fitness r=\r\nemoves the barriers that prevent you from getting strong and healthy and li=\r\nving a full and active life. So, let&#8217;s address your concerns one at a=\r\n time.</p>=0A<ol>=0A<li>Our program requires a commitment of once a week fo=\r\nr 20 minutes. <a href=3D\"http://informfitness.com/workout/how-it-works/\" ta=\r\nrget=3D\"_blank\">That&#8217;s it</a>. with our program.</li>=0A</ol>=0A<p>So, no more excuses, schedule a <a h=\r\nref=3D\"http://informfitness.com/informfitness/contact-us/\" target=3D\"_blank=\r\n\">consultation</a> today &#8211; it is =0D=0A        =\r\n    <section id=3D\"contents\" class=3D\"grid_8\" style=3D\"padding-top:20px;\">=\r\n=0D=0A            \t<div id=3D\"page\">=0D=0A        \t\t                    <di=\r\nv id=3D\"breadcrumbs\">=0D=0A                        <!-- Breadcrumb NavXT 4.=\r\n1.0 -->=0A<span id=3D\"bstart\" style=3D\"color:#666666;font-weight:bold;\">You=\r\n are here:</span> <a style=3D\"color:#666666;\" title=3D\"Go to Home.\" href=3D=\r\n\"http://informfitness.com\">Home</a> &gt; <a style=3D\"color:#666666;\" title=\r\n=3D\"Go to Workout.\" href=3D\"http://informfitness.com/workout/\">Workout</a> =\r\n&gt; How It Works                    </div>                \t=0D=0A         =\r\n       \t<h2>How It Works </h2>=0D=0A                    <h2>The World=E2=80=\r\n=99s Most Efficient Conditioning Workout</h2>=0A<p><img class=3D\"alignleft\"=\r\n style=3D\"width: 300px; height: 200px; border: 1px solid #cccccc; padding: =\r\n2px; margin: 10px;\" title=3D\"How it Works\" src=3D\"http://informfitness.com/=\r\nwp-content/uploads/2012/06/how-it-works.jpg\" alt=3D\"How it Works\" width=3D\"=\r\n500\" height=3D\"334\" /></p>=0A<p><strong>Slow Builds Strength:</strong></p>=\r\n=0A<p><em><strong>We lift weights slowly!</strong></em>=C2=A0We reduce the =\r\nspeed of each repetition to a snail=E2=80=99s pace, a cycle of 10 seconds u=\r\np and 10 seconds down, with no rest between.</p>=0A<p>When you slow down th=\r\ne reps, your muscles work harder because they are not relying on momentum t=\r\no propel your movements. And, because your movement is less herky-jerky, th=\r\ne risk of injury is reduced.</p>=0A<p>InForm Fitness is home to the Power o=\r\nf 10 =E2=80=93 a high-intensity, slow motion, resistance training workout t=\r\nhat provides a week=E2=80=99s worth of exercise in 20 minutes.</p>=0A<block=\r\nquote><p>The Power of 10 philosophy is not only sound clinically but remark=\r\nably effective.</p>=0A<p>=E2=80=93 Fulton C. Kornack, M.D., Clinical Facult=\r\ny in Orthopedic Surgery, Harvard Medical School</p></blockquote>=0A<p>Only =\r\nfive to seven exercises complete a total body workout using our equipment w=\r\nith one of our trainers. We guide you through each set of exercise so that =\r\nthe weights are lifted in slow but continuous movements until the point at =\r\nwhich the muscles can no longer perform. This point is called muscle failur=\r\ne.</p>=0A<p>It may sound easy, but rest assured =E2=80=93 it=E2=80=99s not.=\r\n The goal is to work the muscle to the point of complete exhaustion, known =\r\nas muscle failure, by using high-intensity resistance and a focused, slow w=\r\neight lifting technique =E2=80=93 10 seconds to lift the weight and 10 seco=\r\nnds to lower.</p>=0A<h3>Less Hustle =3D More Muscle</h3>=0A<p>Our focus is =\r\non building and maintaining muscle, because, as we age, we lose lean muscle=\r\n mass. This can result in obesity, diabetes, osteoporosis, chronic pain, an=\r\nd an alarming variety of other health problems.</p>=0A<p>Building muscle is=\r\n the best way to proactively combat these problems, as well as supercharge =\r\nyour metabolism and increase cardiovascular endurance. If your =E2=80=9Cget=\r\n up and go=E2=80=9D has gotten up and gone, then resistance training is the=\r\n way to go starting now =E2=80=93 and the Power of 10 workout is the safest=\r\n and most effective way to resistance train. You=E2=80=99ll see and feel th=\r\ne results in as little as a few weeks =E2=80=93 but the benefits of maintai=\r\nning your program will last a lifetime.</p>=0A<p>You work one-on-one with a=\r\n personal trainer to do six to seven exercises on custom-designed weight ma=\r\nchines for 20 minutes =E2=80=93 just once a week. That=E2=80=99s how long i=\r\nt takes to keep you strong and vital so that you can enjoy an active life! =\r\nInForm Fitness is the ideal personal training studio for anyone who wants t=\r\no get in optimal shape without putting in long and tedious hours at the gym=\r\n.</p>=0A<p>After your workout, we advise a resting period of at least 4 to =\r\n7 days. During this recovery time, your body will actually build thicker an=\r\nd stronger muscle fibers. This concept is supported by a recent publication=\r\n in the <a href=3D\"http://jp.physoc.org/content/543/3/1047.full?sid=3D8cf55=\r\n42c-524f-42ac-b017-0fd655a86a8f\" target=3D\"_blank\">Journal of Physiology</a=\r\n>. This leaves your body time to recover while still burning fat even days =\r\nlater, and plenty of time to live your life to the fullest and participate =\r\nin activities that bring you pleasure and joy.</p>=0A\t\t\t\t   =0D=0A         =\r\n       </div>=0D=0A                =0D=0A                =0D=0A            =\r\n    <span class=3D\"clear\">&nbsp;</span> =0D=0A                <!-- main con=\r\ntents ends -->=0D=0A            </section>\t=0D=0A            \t\t=0D=0A\t\t\t   =\r\n         <section id=3D\"sidebars\" class=3D\"grid_4 pageside\">=0D=0A         =\r\n   \t<div 4.=\r\n1.0 -->=0A<span id=3D\"bstart\" style=3D\"color:#666666;font-weight:bold;\">You=\r\n are here:</span> <a style=3D\"color:#666666;\" title=3D\"Go to Home.\"             </div>                \t=0D=0A            =\r\n    \t<h2>Why Slow? </h2>=0D=0A                    <h2>The Three Benefits of=\r\n Slower Resistance Training<strong></strong></h2>=0A<p><img style=3D\"border=\r\n: 1px solid #ccc; padding: 2px; margin: 10px;\" title=3D\"Why Slow?\" src=3D\"h=\r\nttp://informfitness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/whygoslow.jpg\" alt=3D\"Wh=\r\ny Slow?\" /></p>=0A<p><strong><em></em></strong><br />=0A<strong>YOUR SAFETY=\r\n</strong><br />=0ASlow lifting reduces the forces that commonly cause injur=\r\ny to your joints, muscles and connective tissue.</p>=0A<p><strong>EFFICIENC=\r\nY</strong><br />=0ASlow lifting reduces momentum, which requires the muscle=\r\n to do most of the work. As a result, muscle failure is reached in a minimu=\r\nm amount of time=C2=A0thereby giving you a more efficient workout. When you=\r\n can no longer move the weight, the stimulus for muscle growth has begun.</=\r\np>=0A<p><strong>RESULTS</strong><br />=0AArmed with the knowledge that you =\r\ncan train without injury, you will have the confidence to push your muscles=\r\n to the required level of fatigue, making your workout more effective.</p>=\r\n=0A<blockquote><p>=C2=A0<em>I really don=E2=80=99t enjoy exercising but I l=\r\nove the benefits of feeling fit, being strong and having energy. I=E2=80=99=\r\nve got all three in abundance thanks to InForm Fitness, where I=E2=80=99ve =\r\nbeen exercising for only 20 minutes a week for the last year and a half. It=\r\n=E2=80=99s not magic=E2=80=94it=E2=80=99s hard, controlled work=E2=80=94but=\r\n for only 20 minutes a week! Amazing but true. -=C2=A0<strong>LIDA ORZECK, =\r\n=C2=A0OWNER, HANKY PANKY</strong></em></p></blockquote>=0A\t\t\t\t   =0D=0A    =\r\n            </div>=0D=0A                =0D=0A styl=\r\ne=3D\"padding-top:20px;\">=0D=0A            \t<div id=3D\"page\">=0D=0A        \t=\r\n\t                    <div id=3D\"breadcrumbs\">=0D=0A                        =\r\n<!-- Breadcrumb NavXT 4.1.0 -->=0A<span id=3D\"bstart\" style=3D\"color:#66666=\r\n6;font-weight:bold;\">You are here:</span> <a style=3D\"color:#666666;\" title=\r\n=3D\"Go to Home.\" href=3D\"http://informfitness.com\">Home</a> &gt; <a style=\r\n=3D\"color:#666666;\" title=3D\"Go to Workout.\" href=3D\"http://informfitness.c=\r\nom/workout/\">Workout</a> &gt; Why Rest?                    </div>          =\r\n      \t=0D=0A                \t<h2>Why Rest? </h2>=0D=0A                    =\r\n<h3>Why is rest and recovery such a critical aspect of the <em>Power of 10<=\r\n/em> workout?</h3>=0A<p>The <em>Power of 10</em> workout and rest are the y=\r\nin and the yang of muscle building. It=E2=80=99s a physiological fact that =\r\nyour body needs sufficient time for rest and recovery. You need to eat well=\r\n and strength train, but you also need to sit back, relax, and let your bod=\r\ny do what it needs to do, if you want to meet your goals.</p>=0A<p>Once you=\r\n have worked your muscles to the point of true muscular failure, those musc=\r\nles require sufficient time to repair and restore torn muscle fibers and bu=\r\nild new muscle mass. This process can be enhanced only with proper nutritio=\r\nn, hydration, and the luck of genetics. The best thing you can do is rest a=\r\nnd recover after a workout.</p>=0A<h3>How long should I rest before working=\r\n out again?</h3>=0A<p>Most people believe that going back to the gym after =\r\ntwo days of rest in between workouts is perfectly safe. Not true!</p>=0A<p>=\r\nIf you=E2=80=99re pushing your muscles to the point of total muscle failure=\r\n (as you should), your body needs to rest for much longer than a paltry two=\r\n days. In fact, some of the critical repair work that must occur in muscles=\r\n post-exercise doesn=E2=80=99t even begin until well past the two-day mark.=\r\n You should allow yourself at least five days of full recovery, if not more=\r\n.</p>=0A<h3>Is there such a thing as too much rest?</h3>=0A<p>Absolutely. M=\r\nuscles do atrophy, and for optimal results, you want to=E2=80=A8 continuall=\r\ny build muscle and maintain what you=E2=80=99ve built. Ideally, you should =\r\nrest for 5-7 days, and then work out again. You and your InForm Fitness =E2=\r\n=80=A8personal instructor can decide what the right amount of rest is for y=\r\nou.</p>=0A<p>&nbsp;</p>=0A\t\t\t\t   =0D=0A                </div>=0D=0A        =\r\n 4.1.0 -->=0A<span id=3D\"bstart\" style=3D\"color:#66666=\r\n6;font-weight:bold;\">You are here:</span> <a style=3D\"color:#666666;\" title=\r\n=3D\"Go to Home.\" href=3D\"http://informfitness.com\">Home</a> &gt; Pregnancy =\r\n                   </div>                \t=0D=0A                \t<h2>Pregna=\r\nncy </h2>=0D=0A                    <h2>Can I Exercise While I Am Pregnant?<=\r\n/h2>=0A<p>All pregnancies are different, and before you make any decisions =\r\nregarding your pregnancy and exercise you should check with your doctor fir=\r\nst. Once your doctor has cleared you for physical activity, sensible exerci=\r\nse is terrific conditioning for giving birth.</p>=0A<p>Labor and delivery a=\r\nre extremely strenuous, and the best way to prepare for them is not to lie =\r\non the couch, but to train like an athlete would for any major event. Often=\r\n, women allow themselves to become=C2=A0extremely unconditioned during preg=\r\nnancy. This is a mistake, and can lead not only to a more difficult labor, =\r\nbut also to a more arduous recovery after the birth of your child.</p>=0A<p=\r\n>We=E2=80=99ve had several clients who worked out with us until the middle =\r\nof their eighth month with extremely positive results. If your doctor says =\r\nit=E2=80=99s all right for you to exercise while pregnant, then do it. You =\r\nwon=E2=80=99t regret it.</p>=0A<h3>How Soon After Giving Birth Can I Resume=\r\n My Weekly Workouts?</h3>=0A<p>Individual recoveries may be different, but =\r\nmost women can feel confident resuming their previous level of exercise six=\r\n weeks after giving birth. Once again we encourage you to check with your d=\r\noctor first.</p>=0A\t\t\t\t   =0D=0A                </div>=0D=0A               =\r\n =0D=0A                =0D=0A                <span \t<h2>Worko=\r\nut Results </h2>=0D=0A                    <h2>Safe Efficient Exercise</h2>=\r\n=0A<p>When we talk about InForm Fitness and the <em>Power of 10</em> method=\r\n we are talking about a scientifically proven method to get the optimal res=\r\nults in minimal time. And because of the method employed, it is also the sa=\r\nfest exercise you can perform.</p>=0A<p><strong>It is safe</strong> for mos=\r\nt anyone at any age or stage of life. The slow continuous motion of the <em=\r\n>Power of 10</em> resistance training prevents the abrupt motions that typi=\r\ncally cause muscle tears, joint pains or dislocations. Because there is no =\r\njarring motion like what you experience in aerobics or running, there is no=\r\n risk of damage to your bones or skeletal trauma.</p>=0A<p><strong>It is ef=\r\nficient</strong> because this process takes your muscles into a state of fa=\r\nilure quickly =E2=80=93 this state of failure is necessary for your muscles=\r\n to become stronger. The beauty is that as you build more muscle your body =\r\ncontinues to burn calories long after you have left the gym. That is the he=\r\night of efficiency.</p>=0A<p>The results speak for themselves and our clien=\r\nts describe their results best, which you can read on out <a href=3D\"http:/=\r\n/informfitness.com/workout-results/testimonials/\">testimonials</a> page.</p>=\r\n=0A<p>There are positive changes you can expect to experience ranging from =\r\nstaving off <a href=3D\"http://informfitness.com/workout-results/osteo/\">ost=\r\neoporosis </a>to improved <a href=3D\"http://informfitness.com/workout-resul=\r\nts/bone-density/\">bone density</a>; <a href=3D\"h=\r\nttp://informfitness.com/workout-results/cardio/\">cardio</a> and even an <a =\r\nhref=3D\"http://informfitness.com/workout-results/improve-golf-game/\">improv=\r\ned golf game</a>.</p>=0A<p>We invite you to explore the benefits of the <em=\r\n>Power of 10</em> workout offered at InForm Fitness and investigate our <a            \t<div id=3D\"=\r\npage\">=0D=0A        \t\t                    <div id=3D\"breadcrumbs\">=0D=0A   =\r\n                     <!-- Breadcrumb NavXT 4.1.0 -->=0A<span id=3D\"bstart\" =\r\nstyle=3D\"color:#666666;font-weight:bold;\">You are here:</span> <a style=3D\"=\r\ncolor:#666666;\" title=3D\"Go to Home.\" href=3D\"http://informfitness.com\">Hom=\r\ne</a> &gt; <a style=3D\"color:#666666;\" title=3D\"Go to Workout Results.\" hre=\r\nf=3D\"http://informfitness.com/workout-results/\">Workout Results</a> &gt; Os=\r\nteo                    </div>                \t=0D=0A                \t<h2>Os=\r\nteo </h2>=0D=0A                    <h2>Can I Work Out If I Have Osteoporosi=\r\ns?</h2>=0A<p><img style=3D\"float: left; width: 300px; height: 200px; border=\r\n: 1px solid #ccc; padding: 2px; margin: 10px;\" title=3D\"Osteo\" src=3D\"http:=\r\n//informfitness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/osteo.jpg\" alt=3D\"Osteo\" /><=\r\n/p>=0A<p>If you=E2=80=99re one of the eight million American women sufferin=\r\ng from osteoporosis (or among the 44 million Americans at risk for contract=\r\ning the disease), you may worry that any strenuous physical activity could =\r\ncause a fracture or other injury. Surprisingly, studies show that one of th=\r\ne best things that you can do to counteract bone loss is to strength train!=\r\n</p>=0A<p>The world-renowned Mayo Clinic advises those with osteoporosis to=\r\n engage in low force strength training or other load bearing activities tha=\r\nt will strengthen the muscle and bone, slowing loss of bone mineral, and to=\r\n avoid high-impact cardio exercise such as jogging, or high force strength =\r\ntraining. If you have osteoporosis, the best way to exercise is through slo=\r\nw, high-intensity strength training like the Power of 10 program =E2=80=93 =\r\nbut talk to your doctor first.</p>=0A<p>Learn what the <a href=3D\"http://ww=\r\nw.mayoclinic.com/health/osteoporosis/HQ00643\" target=3D\"_blank\">experts</a>=\r\n at the Mayo Clinic have to say on this topic.</p>=0A<p>And we can recommen=\r\nd Dr. Miriam E. Nelson&#8217;s book: <a href=3D\"http://www.amazon.com/gp/pr=\r\noduct/0399532498?ie=3DUTF8&amp;tag=3Dwwwstrengthtr20&amp;linkCode=3Das2&amp=\r\n;camp=3D1789&amp;creative=3D9325&amp;creativeASIN=3D0399532498\" target=3D\"_=\r\nblank\">Strong Women, Strong Bones</a></p>=0A<p><em><strong>Quick Tip:</stro=\r\nng></em> Soda isn=E2=80=99t doing your bones any favors. If you=E2=80=99ve =\r\ngiven up sugary soft drinks for your health, you=E2=80=99re on the right tr=\r\nack=E2=80=94but even the diet stuff is proven to lower your bone density. I=\r\nn=C2=A0fact, in <a href=3D\"http://www.medpagetoday.com/Endocrinology/Osteop=\r\norosis/4247\" target=3D\"_blank\">a recent study published</a> in the American=\r\n Journal of Clinical Nutrition, women who drank soda of any kind on a daily=\r\n basis had bone density levels between three and five percent lower than wo=\r\nmen who only drank a can a month. Our suggestion, switch to water, and do y=\r\nour bones a huge favor.</p>=0A<p>&nbsp;</p>=0A<p>&nbsp;</p>=0A<p>&nbsp;</p>=\r\n=0A\t\t\t\t   =0D=0A                </div>=0D=0A                =0D=0A         =\r\n       =0D=0A                <span class=3D\"clear\">&nbsp;</span> =0D=0A    =\r\n            <!-- main contents ends -->=0D=0A            </section>\t=0D=0A =\r\n           \t\t=0D=0A\t\t\t            <section id=3D\"sidebars\" class=3D\"grid_4 =\r\npageside\">=0D=0A            \t<div class=3D\"pagetop\">&nbsp;</div>=0D=0A     =\r\n           <div class=3D\"posts\" style=3D\"padding-left: 15px;\">=0D=0A\t\t\t\t =\r\n=0D=0A                =0D=0A=0D=0A                            <section id=\r\n=3D\"side_follows\" style=3D\"margin-top: -20px; margin-bottom: 20px;\">=0D=0A =\r\n =0D=0A            <se=\r\nction id=3D\"contents\" class=3D\"grid_8\" style=3D\"padding-top:20px;\">=0D=0A  =\r\n          \t<div id=3D\"page\">=0D=0A        \t\t                    <div id=3D\"=\r\nbreadcrumbs\">=0D=0A                        <!-- Breadcrumb NavXT 4.1.0 -->=\r\n=0A<span id=3D\"bstart\" style=3D\"color:#666666;font-weight:bold;\">You are he=\r\nre:</span> <a style=3D\"color:#666666;\" title=3D\"Go to Home.\" href=3D\"http:/=\r\n/informfitness.com\">Home</a> &gt; <a style=3D\"color:#666666;\" title=3D\"Go t=\r\no Workout Results.\" href=3D\"http://informfitness.com/workout-results/\">Work=\r\nout Results</a> &gt; Strength                    </div>                \t=0D=\r\n=0A                \t<h2>Strength </h2>=0D=0A                    <h2>We Can =\r\nImprove Your Strength By Building Muscle</h2>=0A<p><img style=3D\"float: lef=\r\nt; width: 300px; height: 200px; border: 1px solid #ccc; padding: 2px; margi=\r\nn: 10px;\" title=3D\"Strength\" src=3D\"http://informfitness.com/wp-content/upl=\r\noads/2012/06/strength.jpg\" alt=3D\"Strength\" /></p>=0A<p>We all can benefit =\r\nfrom strength building. If you are like most people, you&#8217;ve been face=\r\nd with a task or a routine that gives you pause as you wonder if you are st=\r\nrong enough to accept the challenge. =C2=A0We all remember a day when we &#=\r\n8216;could have&#8217; and with the <em>Power of 10</em> strength training,=\r\n we think you still can.</p>=0A<blockquote><p>&nbsp;</p></blockquote>=0A<h3=\r\n>I want to look lean and sculpted but not bulked up.</h3>=0A<p>Relax =E2=80=\r\n=93 and then start working out! Very few people are genetically predisposed=\r\n to look like Mr. Olympia, and if you=E2=80=99re one of those very few, you=\r\n probably already know it. The truth is, muscle always looks better than fa=\r\nt, and if you are looking for an aesthetic improvement as well as a healthy=\r\n one, muscle building is still the way to go.</p>=0A<p>=E2=80=9CBulking up=\r\n=E2=80=9D is dependent on several variables, many of which are entirely gen=\r\netic. Most people simply do not have the inherited traits necessary to deve=\r\nlop the enormous muscles people have begun to associate with weight trainin=\r\ng, and in fact have inherited systems that guard against developing too muc=\r\nh muscle.</p>=0A<p>Myostatin is just one of these biological mechanisms. My=\r\nostatin, also known as growth differentiation factor 8, abbreviated &#8220;=\r\nGDF8&#8243;, is a secreted TGF beta protein family member that inhibits mus=\r\ncle differentiation and growth. Myostatin is one of a number of built-in go=\r\nvernors in the human body that ensures your body is comprised of more than =\r\njust muscle, so that you can survive during times of famine. Most people ha=\r\nve enough myostatin in their system to avoid turning into the Incredible Hu=\r\nlk. If you=E2=80=99ve ever done any weight training and you aren=E2=80=99t =\r\nalready muscle-bound, you=E2=80=99re not going to be after <em>Power of 10<=\r\n/em> =E2=80=93 but you will be in much better shape.</p>=0A<p>Printed in th=\r\ne Journal of Physiology: A practical model of low-volume high-intensity int=\r\nerval training induces mitochondrial biogenesis in human skeletal muscle: p=\r\notential mechanisms. <a href=3D\"http://jp.physoc.org/content/early/2010/01/=\r\n20/jphysiol.2009.181743.abstract\" target=3D\"_blank\">This study</a> demonstr=\r\nates=C2=A0High-intensity interval training (HIT) induces skeletal muscle me=\r\ntabolic and performance adaptations that resemble traditional endurance tra=\r\nining despite a low total exercise volume.</p>=0A\t\t\t\t class=3D\"clear\">&nbsp;</s=\r\npan>=0D=0A        <section id=3D\"maincontents\">=0D=0A        =0D=0A        =\r\n    <section id=3D\"contents\" class=3D\"grid_8\" style=3D\"padding-top:20px;\">=\r\n=0D=0A            \t<div id=3D\"page\">=0D=0A        \t\t                    <di=\r\nv id=3D\"breadcrumbs\">=0D=0A                        <!-- Breadcrumb NavXT 4.=\r\n1.0 -->=0A<span id=3D\"bstart\" style=3D\"color:#666666;font-weight:bold;\">You=\r\n are here:</span> <a style=3D\"color:#666666;\" title=3D\"Go to Home.\" href=3D=\r\n\"http://informfitness.com\">Home</a> &gt; <a style=3D\"color:#666666;\" title=\r\n=3D\"Go to Workout Results.\" href=3D\"http://informfitness.com/workout-result=\r\ns/\">Workout Results</a> &gt; Diabetes                    </div>            =\r\n    \t=0D=0A                \t<h2>Diabetes </h2>=0D=0A                    <p>=\r\n<img style=3D\"float: left; width: 300px; height: 200px; border: 1px solid #=\r\nccc; padding: 2px; margin: 10px;\" title=3D\"diabetes\" src=3D\"http://informfi=\r\ntness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/diabetes2.jpg\" alt=3D\"diabetes\" /><br =\r\n/>=0A<strong>Diabetes </strong>is a group of metabolic diseases in which a =\r\nperson has high=C2=A0blood sugar, either because the body does not produce =\r\nenough=C2=A0insulin, or because cells do not respond to the insulin that is=\r\n produced.</p>=0A<p>This high blood sugar produces the classical symptoms o=\r\nf=C2=A0polyuria=C2=A0(frequent urination),=C2=A0polydipsia=C2=A0(increased =\r\nthirst) and polyphagia=C2=A0(increased hunger). All forms of diabetes have =\r\nbeen treatable since=C2=A0insulin=C2=A0became available in 1921, and type=\r\n=C2=A02 diabetes may be controlled with medications. Both types 1 and 2 are=\r\n=C2=A0chronic=C2=A0conditions that usually cannot be cured.</p>=0A<p>Adequa=\r\nte treatment of diabetes is thus important, as well as=C2=A0blood pressure=\r\n=C2=A0control and lifestyle factors such as=C2=A0smoking=C2=A0cessation and=\r\n maintaining a healthy=C2=A0body weight.</p>=0A<p><em><strong>How Can The P=\r\nower of 10 Help With Diabetes?</strong></em></p>=0A<h2>Simply Stated &#8211=\r\n; Better Insulin Control</h2>=0A<p>If you are pre or destined to be a diabe=\r\ntic, there are many things you can to to stave off the disease. If you have=\r\n diabetes already, the <em>Power of 10</em> can help you get your diabetes =\r\nunder control.</p>=0A<p>To burn more fat, it=E2=80=99s essential to keep yo=\r\nur blood sugar levels low. A <em>Power of 10</em> workout will deplete your=\r\n muscles of stored sugar, aka, glycogen, and in essence increase your muscl=\r\nes appetite for sugar.</p>=0A<p>In conjunction with a low-carbohydrate diet=\r\n, and with your muscles sucking up any remaining sugar, insulin levels are =\r\nsuppressed =E2=80=93 and that=E2=80=99s a good thing. It triggers your stre=\r\nss hormones, adrenaline, and epinephrine to activate a process to metaboliz=\r\ne large amounts of fat (aka triacylglycerol) to be used for fuel. Too much =\r\nblood sugar, however, derails this process. Your insulin will block fat met=\r\nabolism and will instead direct that sugar to be stored as fat.</p>=0A<p>Th=\r\ne combination of <em>Power of 10=E2=80=99s</em> high-intensity exercise and=\r\n a diet low in carbs will help you shed fat as efficiently as possible and =\r\ngain control over your insulin.</p>=0A\t\t\t\t   =0D=0A                </div>=\r\n=0D=0A                =0D=0A -->=0D=0A        =0D=0A=0D=0A        <!-- end of slideshow -->=\r\n=0D=0A        =0D=0A        <span class=3D\"clear\">&nbsp;</span>=0D=0A      =\r\n  <section id=3D\"maincontents\">=0D=0A        =0D=0A            <section id=\r\n=3D\"contents\" class=3D\"grid_8\" style=3D\"padding-top:20px;\">=0D=0A          =\r\n  \t<div id=3D\"page\">=0D=0A        \t\t                    <div id=3D\"breadcru=\r\nmbs\">=0D=0A                        <!-- Breadcrumb NavXT 4.1.0 -->=0A<span =\r\nid=3D\"bstart\" style=3D\"color:#666666;font-weight:bold;\">You are here:</span=\r\n> <a style=3D\"color:#666666;\" title=3D\"Go to Home.\" href=3D\"http://informfi=\r\ntness.com\">Home</a> &gt; <a style=3D\"color:#666666;\" title=3D\"Go to Workout=\r\n Results.\" href=3D\"http://informfitness.com/workout-results/\">Workout Resul=\r\nts</a> &gt; Cardio                    </div>                \t=0D=0A        =\r\n        \t<h2>Cardio </h2>=0D=0A                    <p>It=E2=80=99s undeniab=\r\nle. Cardio is important. But just what kind of exercise promotes cardio hea=\r\nlth? Running, aerobics, high-impact training, spinning, and so on? True, th=\r\nese are all well-known cardio exercises. But for most people that=E2=80=99s=\r\n a huge and unrealistic time commitment! And will you really go to the gym =\r\nevery day, and have you weighed the risks?</p>=0A<h3>The Risk Of Too Little=\r\n Cardio:</h3>=0A<p>If you bike, jog, or hop on the elliptical trainer, for =\r\none or two half-hour sessions a week, you may burn about 200-300 calories f=\r\nor that week. But, you certainly won=E2=80=99t build enough muscle to see a=\r\nn increase in your metabolism, and you definitely won=E2=80=99t burn enough=\r\n calories to put a real dent in your fat loss. A pound of fat is 3,500 calo=\r\nries! Sporadic cardio simply doesn=E2=80=99t cut it!</p>=0A<h3>The Risk Of =\r\nToo Much Cardio:</h3>=0A<p>If you really can devote between 30-60 minutes e=\r\nvery day, or almost every day, to high-intensity cardio, then you will cert=\r\nainly build some muscle and you=E2=80=99ll burn some calories. If you=E2=80=\r\n=99re eating well, you may even see some significant fat loss. But here=E2=\r\n=80=99s the (pardon our pun) BIG BUT: Pounding away at your joints for an h=\r\nour every day is your body=E2=80=99s worst nightmare!</p>=0A<p>Such force c=\r\nan lead to short-term problems, such as shin splints, sprained ankles, and =\r\ntendonitis. Even worse, that force can lead to long-term major concerns, in=\r\ncluding arthritis and damaged joints, cardiovascular disease, and a lowered=\r\n immune system. Almost nobody walks away from a lifetime of pounding the pa=\r\nvement totally unscathed. To further contribute to the idea of Too Much Car=\r\ndio, recent studies have shown results that indicate prolonged and intense =\r\ncardio exercise being linked to heart damage. (Published study can be found=\r\n <a href=3D\"http://circ.ahajournals.org/content/123/1/13.short\">American He=\r\nart Association</a>.)</p>=0A<h3>Do The Math:</h3>=0A<p>One pound is 3,500 c=\r\nalories. If you burn 150 calories on a treadmill in an hour, that means you=\r\n require 23 hours on that treadmill to burn one pound. That=E2=80=99s 3 hou=\r\nrs a day, 7 days a week.</p>=0A<h3>The Secret Advantage In Strength Trainin=\r\ng:</h3>=0A<p>The <em>Power of 10</em> strength building exercises gives you=\r\n a metabolic spike for an hour after a workout. This phenomenon occurs beca=\r\nuse your body is trying to help your muscles recover. That means you&#8217;=\r\nll be burning an additional 25 percent of the calories you just burned away=\r\n during your strength session. More math: if you burned 200 calories in one=\r\n of our 20-minute workouts, it&#8217;s really closer to 250 calories total.=\r\n</p>=0A<p>If that wasn&#8217;t enough incentive to get you hoping into a ca=\r\nb and racing over to InForm Fitness, add these numbers into the equation: f=\r\nor every 3 pounds of muscle you build with us, you&#8217;ll burn an additio=\r\nnal 120 calories a day with no additional exercise, simply because muscle r=\r\nequires more energy to sustain. That could amount to about 10 pounds of wei=\r\nght loss a year while you are just sitting there.=C2=A0<a href=3D\"http://ww=\r\nw.womenshealthmag.com/fitness/cardio-vs-strength-training-workouts#ixzz1xRZ=\r\nHvpiS\" target=3D\"_blank\">Read more</a> at Women&#8217;s Health.</p>=0A<p>Of=\r\n course you could always follow our regime instead, with one 20 minute week=\r\nly session with <em>Power of 10</em> to help you lose more fat faster, more=\r\n efficiently, and without the risk of injury.</p>=0A<h3>But What About My H=\r\neart?:</h3>=0A<p>Your heart is a muscular organ.=C2=A0The heart is principa=\r\nlly composed of cardiac muscle and connective tissue and its primary functi=\r\non is to pump blood. By taking muscles to the point of muscle failure in th=\r\ne <em>Power of 10</em> workout, we are increasing blood flow and stimulatin=\r\ng the heart to work harder providing a cardio workout as part of the proces=\r\ns.</p>=0A<div></div>=0A\t\t\t\t   =0D=0A                </div>=0D=0A           =\r\n     =0D=0A                =0D=0A                <span class=3D\"clear\">&nbs=\r\np;</span> =0D=0A                <!-- main contents ends -->=0D=0A          =\r\n  </section>\t=0D=0A            \t\t=0D=0A\t\t\t            <section id=3D\"sideba=\r\nrs\" class=3D\"grid_4 pageside\">=0D=0A            \t<div class=3D\"pagetop\">&nb=\r\nsp;</div>=0D=0A                <div class=3D\"posts\" style=3D\"padding-left: =\r\n15px;\">=0D=0A\t\t\t\t =0D=0A                =0D=0A=0D=0A class=3D\"sub-menu\">=0A\t<li id=3D\"menu-item-154\" class=\r\n=3D\"menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-object-page menu-item-154\"=\r\n><a end of Hea=\r\nder -->=0D=0A        =0D=0A=0D=0A        <!-- end of slideshow -->=0D=0A   =\r\n     =0D=0A        <span class=3D\"clear\">&nbsp;</span>=0D=0A        <sectio=\r\nn id=3D\"maincontents\">=0D=0A        =0D=0A            <section id=3D\"conten=\r\nts\" class=3D\"grid_8\" style=3D\"padding-top:20px;\">=0D=0A            \t<div id=\r\n=3D\"page\">=0D=0A        \t\t                    <div id=3D\"breadcrumbs\">=0D=\r\n=0A                        <!-- Breadcrumb NavXT 4.1.0 -->=0A<span id=3D\"bs=\r\ntart\" style=3D\"color:#666666;font-weight:bold;\">You are here:</span> <a sty=\r\nle=3D\"color:#666666;\" title=3D\"Go to Home.\" href=3D\"http://informfitness.co=\r\nm\">Home</a> &gt; <a style=3D\"color:#666666;\" title=3D\"Go to Workout Results=\r\n.\" href=3D\"http://informfitness.com/workout-results/\">Workout Results</a> &=\r\ngt; Bone Density                    </div>                \t=0D=0A          =\r\n      \t<h2>Bone Density </h2>=0D=0A                    <p><img style=3D\"flo=\r\nat: left; width: 300px; height: 200px; border: 1px solid #ccc; padding: 2px=\r\n; margin: 10px;\" title=3D\"Bone Density\" src=3D\"http://informfitness.com/wp-=\r\ncontent/uploads/2012/06/bone-density.jpg\" alt=3D\"Bone Density\" /></p>=0A<p>=\r\nWhat do we think when we see a magnificent old building still standing tall=\r\n? We usually make a comment to the effect of that building having a great f=\r\noundation. Our bones make up our skeleton, which is our foundation, and for=\r\n us to continue standing tall in our own magnificence, we need to continual=\r\nly be improving our foundation &#8211; our bone density.</p>=0A<p>The key t=\r\no improving your bone density is strength training. Building muscle directl=\r\ny increases bone density by putting increased stress on the bones, making t=\r\nhem stronger, healthier, and less prone to fractures and breaks. Not only d=\r\noes increased bone density slow the devastating bone loss associated with=\r\n=C2=A0getting older, it also helps to counteract any future loss by buildin=\r\ng additional bone matter.</p>=0A<p><em><strong>How &#8211; You Ask?</strong=\r\n></em></p>=0A<p>Muscle building spurs the osteoblasts which are the crucial=\r\n cells responsible for building new bone mineral. Your new muscle mass will=\r\n also serve to protect your bones, guarding them against injury and cushion=\r\ning the blow in case of a fall.</p>=0A<p>There are numerous benefits from r=\r\nesistance training to improve bone density, which to name but a few, are in=\r\ncreased bone mineral density, increased strength, and an increased ability =\r\nto perform activities. You can read more from a recent study=C2=A0<a href=\r\n=3D\"www.unm.edu/~lkravitz/Article%20folder/bonemass.html\">=E2=80=9CThe Bene=\r\nfits of Strength Training for Bone Density=E2=80=9D</a></p>=0A<p>And if you=\r\nr curiosity has been piqued, have you ever wondered why young astronauts of=\r\nten have the bones of much older people? To further prove our position that=\r\n supports resistance training, astronauts lose bone mass rapidly because th=\r\neir bones aren=E2=80=99t working against the force of gravity on Earth=C2=\r\n=A0while floating in space. You can <a href=3D\"www.space.com/scienceastrono=\r\nmy/090126-astronauts-bone-strength-loss.html\" target=3D\"_blank\">read about =\r\nthis phenomenon</a>.</p>=0A<blockquote><p>It is an accepted fact in the fie=\r\nld of orthopedics that resistance training serves as the core of any succes=\r\nsful, healthy conditioning program. This is true for people of all ages, fr=\r\nom adolescents to senior citizens. Enhanced strength through resistance tra=\r\nining helps to stabilize and protect the body&#8217;s joints. This not only=\r\n prevents injury, but improves performance. It has the added benefit of red=\r\nucing stress on arthritic joints in the older population, which results in =\r\nreduced symptoms and increased function. And for overall health, the lean m=\r\nuscle it generates plays a vital role in metabolizing and &#8220;burning&#8=\r\n221; excess body fat. (Excerpt by Fulton C. Kornack, MD., Clinical Faculty =\r\nin Orthopedic Surgery, Harvard Medical School, The Power of 10)</p></blockq=\r\nuote>=0A<p>&nbsp;</p>=0A<p>&nbsp;</p>=0A<p>&nbsp;</p>=0A\t\t\t\t   =0D=0A      =\r\n          </div>=0D=0A                =0D=0A                =0D=0A         =\r\n       <span class=3D\"clear\">&nbsp;</span> =0D=0A                <!-- main =\r\ncontents ends -->=0D=0A            </section>\t=0D=0A            \t\t=0D=0A\t\t\t=\r\n            <section id=3D\"sidebars\" class=3D\"grid_4 pageside\">=0D=0A      =\r\n      \t<div class=3D\"pagetop\">&nbsp;</div>=0D=0A                <div class=\r\n=3D\"posts\" style=3D\"padding-left: 15px;\">=0D=0A\t\t\t\t =0D=0A                =\r\n=0D=0A=0D=0A                            <section id=3D\"side_follows\" style=\r\n=3D\"margin-top: id=3D\"breadcrumbs\">=0D=0A                        =\r\n<!-- Breadcrumb NavXT 4.1.0 -->=0A<span id=3D\"bstart\" style=3D\"color:#66666=\r\n6;font-weight:bold;\">You are here:</span> <a style=3D\"color:#666666;\" title=\r\n=3D\"Go to Home.\" href=3D\"http://informfitness.com\">Home</a> &gt; <a style=\r\n=3D\"color:#666666;\" title=3D\"Go to Workout Results.\" href=3D\"http://informf=\r\nitness.com/workout-results/\">Workout Results</a> &gt; Lose Fat             =\r\n       </div>                \t=0D=0A                \t<h2>Lose Fat </h2>=0D=\r\n=0A                    <h2>How Do I Lose Excessive Fat And Weight?</h2>=0A<=\r\np><img style=3D\"float: left; width: 300px; height: 200px; border: 1px solid=\r\n #ccc; padding: 2px; margin: 10px;\" title=3D\"Lose Fat\" src=3D\"http://inform=\r\nfitness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/fat-loss.jpg\" alt=3D\"Lose Fat\" /></p>=\r\n=0A<p>We all say that we want to lose weight but really what we want is to =\r\nlose that flab. We have good news and a dose of reality. Exercise alone is =\r\nnot going to be enough to accomplish that goal. No amount of exercise alone=\r\n can make up for an unbalanced diet, high in the empty calories found in ca=\r\nrbohydrates and sugar that we&#8217;ve come to exist on these days.</p>=0A<=\r\np>InForm Fitness can certainly help you achieve your weight loss goals with=\r\n the <em>Power of 10</em>=C2=A0strength building exercise system as it forc=\r\nes the body to use your excess fat as fuel.</p>=0A<p>By building up your mu=\r\nscle we can help you to lose weight. Muscle makes up of over 40% of our tot=\r\nal body mass and is the greatest consumer of your body=E2=80=99s energy sto=\r\nres. By adding 5-10 lbs. of muscle, you can burn a whopping 300 extra calor=\r\nies a day staying sedentary. That&#8217;s great news right?</p>=0A<p>But th=\r\ne caveat is that you will only lose fat and weight if you also =E2=80=9Ceat=\r\n to lose.=E2=80=9D Healthcare professionals recommend a diet that is low in=\r\n sugar and grain-based carbohydrates, such as pasta, bread, rice, and cerea=\r\nl.</p>=0A<p>This may not be what you wanted to hear =E2=80=93 but there is =\r\nno need to despair. The good news is that you can eat more healthfully and =\r\nwith pleasure, fullness and experience a delicious variety. We have some re=\r\ncommendations for you on our <a href=3D\"http://informfitness.com/resources/=\r\neating-healthy/\">Eating Healthy</a> and <a href=3D\"http://informfitness.com=\r\n/resources/nutritional-guide/\">Nutritional</a> guides. Your new palate will=\r\n dine on high-quality proteins from grass-fed beef, free-roaming chickens a=\r\nnd eggs, and wild-caught seafood, quality fats, organic vegetables, whole m=\r\nilk from grass-fed cows, and moderate amounts of organic fruits. As an InFo=\r\nrm Fitness client we offer tips and advice on healthy eating and we encoura=\r\nge our clients to talk with us about their food choices.</p>=0A<p>As a bala=\r\nnced way of life and not a =E2=80=9Cdiet,=E2=80=9D these nourishing foods w=\r\nill gear your body towards ultimate excess fat loss, physical performance a=\r\nnd superior health. But nobody can claim perfect adherence, so it=E2=80=99s=\r\n okay treat yourself once in awhile . . . within reason!</p>=0A\t\t\t\t   =0D=\r\n=0A                </div>=0D=0A                =0D=0A </h2>=0D=0A                    <p>There is a simple rule to i=\r\nmproving your golf game &#8211; play more golf. The same can be said for te=\r\nnnis or any sport that you enjoy.<br />=0A<img style=3D\"border: 1px solid #=\r\nccc; padding: 2px; margin: 10px;\" title=3D\"Improve Golf Game\" src=3D\"http:/=\r\n/informfitness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/improve-golf-game.jpg\" alt=3D=\r\n\"Improve Golf Game\" /></p>=0A<h3>How Can InForm Fitness Help?</h3>=0A<p>We =\r\ncan help improve your game in several ways. First of all with our once-a-we=\r\nek, 20-minute work out you won&#8217;t be spending all your spare time at t=\r\nhe gym. That means more time on the course perfecting that swing.</p>=0A<p>=\r\nThe strength building you will get from the <em>Power 0f 10</em> workout wi=\r\nll reduce your risk of injury that would otherwise take you out of the game=\r\n.</p>=0A<blockquote><p>A regular exercise program that includes core streng=\r\nthening, stretching and strengthening all the major muscle groups can help =\r\ndecrease your injury rate and increase your playing time. &#8211; John D. C=\r\nampbell, MD, American Orthopaedic</p></blockquote>=0A<p>Strength training w=\r\nith InForm Fitness not only improves your muscle strength but it also impro=\r\nves your joints providing a better shock absorber able to protect you from =\r\ncommon injuries sustained from sports activities. These injuries range from=\r\n general back aches=C2=A0in the lower back, elbows, shoulders, hands and wr=\r\nists.</p>=0A<p>Should you become injured or require surgery for some reason=\r\n, you&#8217;ll discover another benefit from our workout &#8211; reduced re=\r\ncovery time. You will recover faster when your bones and muscles were at pe=\r\nak performance prior to any injury sustained.</p>=0A<p>Golf and other sport=\r\ns related injuries are either cumulative (overuse) or acute (traumatic). Th=\r\ne impact and stress of the repetitive motion of the swing is sometimes hard=\r\n on the muscles and joints. Talk to one of our trainers to develop a routin=\r\ne that will support your love of the game by keeping you on the course and =\r\noff the couch.</p>=0A\t\t\t\t   =0D=0A                </div>=0D=0A             =\r\n   =0D=0A                =0D=0A                <span class=3D\"clear\">&nbsp;=\r\n</span> =0D=0A                <!-- main contents ends -->=0D=0A            =\r\n</section>\t=0D=0A   \t<span class=3D\"time\"></span>9 December, 2011=\r\n                            <span class=3D\"cat\"></span><a href=3D\"http://in=\r\nformfitness.com/blog/category/health/\" title=3D\"View all      <p>From MedPage Today, Dec 6=\r\n, 2011: Intense endurance exercise &#8212; such as running a marathon &#821=\r\n2; may induce cardiac damage confined to the right ventricle, a small study=\r\n showed. Highly trained endurance athletes had reductions in right ventricu=\r\nlar function immediately after a race, although it mostly returned to norma=\r\nl about a week later, according to <a href=3D\"http://informfitness.com/blog=\r\n/strength-test-post/\">Read more&#8230;</a></p>=0A                        =\r\n=0D=0A                        <span class=3D\"clear\" style=3D\"clear:both;\">&=\r\nnbsp;</span>=0D=0A                        =0D=0A                    </secti=\r\non>=0D=0A\t\t\t\t                =0D=0A                 =0D=0A                \t=\r\n<section class=3D\"blogarchives\">=0D=0A                        <h2 class=3D\"=\r\nblogh2\"><a href=3D\"http://informfitness.com/blog/test-post-2/\">The Happines=\r\ns Project</a></h2>=0D=0A                    \t<div class=3D\"meta\">=0D=0A    =\r\n                    \t<span class=3D\"time\"></span>8 December, 2011          =\r\n                  <span class=3D\"cat\"></span><a href=3D\"http://informfitnes=\r\ns.com/blog/category/strength/\" title=3D\"View all posts in Strength\" rel=3D\"=\r\ncategory tag\">Strength</a>                        </div>  =0D=0A           =\r\n             =0D=0A                        <section class=3D\"blog-img\">=0D=\r\n=0A\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img src=3D'http://informfitness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/4=\r\n8_happiness-project-150x150.jpg' class=3D'thumbnail' />                    =\r\n    </section>                      =0D=0A                        <p>We rea=\r\nlly enjoyed this book and wanted to share it with you. class=3D'thumbnail' />                        </section> =\r\n                     =0D=0A                        <p>From MedPage Today, D=\r\nec 6, 2011: Intense endurance exercise &#8212; such as running a marathon &=\r\n#8212; may induce cardiac damage confined to the right ventricle, a small s=\r\ntudy showed. Highly trained endurance athletes had reductions in right vent=\r\nricular function immediately after a race, although it mostly returned to n=\r\normal about a week later, according to <a href=3D\"http://informfitness.com/=\r\nblog/strength-test-post/\">Read more&#8230;</a></p>=0A                      =\r\n  =0D=0A                        <span class=3D\"clear\" style=3D\"clear:both;\"=\r\n>&nbsp;</span>=0D=0A                        =0D=0A                    </sec=\r\ntion>=0D=0A\t\t\t\t                =0D=0A                 =0D=0A               =\r\n \t<section class=3D\"blogarchives\">=0D=0A                        <h2 class=\r\n=3D\"blogh2\"><a href=3D\"http://informfitness.com/blog/test-post-2/\">The Happ=\r\niness Project</a></h2>=0D=0A                    \t<div class=3D\"meta\">=0D=0A=\r\n                        \t<span class=3D\"time\"></span>8 December, 2011      =\r\n                      <span class=3D\"cat\"></span><a href=3D\"http://informfi=\r\ntness.com/blog/category/strength/\" title=3D\"View all posts in Strength\" rel=\r\n=3D\"category tag\">Strength</a>                        </div>  =0D=0A       =\r\n                 =0D=0A                        <section class=3D\"blog-img\">=\r\n=0D=0A\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img src=3D'http://informfitness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/0=\r\n6/48_happiness-project-150x150.jpg' class=3D'thumbnail' />                 =\r\n       </section>                      =0D=0A                        <p>We =\r\nreally enjoyed this book and wanted to share it with you. True, Gretchen Ru=\r\nbin, talks about us in her NY Times Bestselling Book, The Happiness Project=\r\n, which we might add is now in paperback. \t\t                    <div id=3D\"breadcrumbs\">=0D=0A                     =\r\n   <!-- Breadcrumb NavXT 4.1.0 -->=0A<span id=3D\"bstart\" style=3D\"color:#66=\r\n6666;font-weight:bold;\">You are here:</span> <a style=3D\"color:#666666;\" ti=\r\ntle=3D\"Go to Home.\" href=3D\"http://informfitness.com\">Home</a> &gt; <a styl=\r\ne=3D\"color:#666666;\" title=3D\"Go to Resources.\" href=3D\"http://informfitnes=\r\ns.com/resources/\">Resources</a> &gt; FAQs                    </div>        =\r\n        \t=0D=0A                \t<h2>FAQs </h2>=0D=0A                    <h2=\r\n>Answers To Questions You Might Have About Inform Fitness</h2>=0A<div class=\r\n=3D\"clearp\">&nbsp;</div><span class=3D'collapseomatic ' id=3D'id1210'  titl=\r\ne=3D\"What Do I Wear To A Workout?\">What Do I Wear To A Workout?</span>=0A<d=\r\niv id=3D'target-id1210' class=3D'collapseomatic_content '> Gym Clothes Not =\r\nRequired. Our only rule regarding attire is no skirts, heels, or restrictiv=\r\ne clothing. You are welcome to wear gym clothes if you wish, but business c=\r\nasual or street clothing is also appropriate. Whatever you wear, just be su=\r\nre that your muscles and joints can enjoy an unrestricted and full range of=\r\n motion.</div>=0A<div class=3D\"clearl\">&nbsp;</div>=0A<div class=3D\"clearp\"=\r\n>&nbsp;</div><span class=3D'collapseomatic ' id=3D'id9290'  title=3D\"I Hear=\r\n You Don't Sweat - Is That True?\">I Hear You Don't Sweat - Is That True?</s=\r\npan>=0A<div id=3D'target-id9290' class=3D'collapseomatic_content '> Well, y=\r\nou may hear that, but it&#8217;s not quite true. InForm Fitness exercise st=\r\nudios are intentionally kept at a comfortably cool (68F) temperature at all=\r\n times, not to prevent sweating, but to prevent overheating. Overheating is=\r\n the stage where sweating no longer helps cool you down, but may reduce per=\r\nformance and lead to nausea and/or other more serious conditions. So, while=\r\n some people are more prone to sweating than others, not many people sweat =\r\nhere.</div>=0A<div class=3D\"clearl\">&nbsp;</div>=0A<div class=3D\"clearp\">&n=\r\nbsp;</div><span class=3D'collapseomatic ' id=3D'id286'  title=3D\"Must I Hav=\r\ne A Personal Trainer?\">Must I Have A Personal Trainer?</span>=0A<div id=3D'=\r\ntarget-id286' class=3D'collapseomatic_content '> Yes. Each workout is condu=\r\ncted under the close supervision and guidance of a highly trained instructo=\r\nr. This is good for safety, good for keeping you motivated, good for ensuri=\r\nng that you=E2=80=99re maintaining proper form, and good for tracking your =\r\nprogress.</p>=0A<p>At InForm Fitness, you never have to worry about setting=\r\n up the machines or charting your progress. Our instructors are responsible=\r\n for designing the workout, setting up the machines, and motivating you thr=\r\nough the tough and final repetitions of each exercise, and all the while ke=\r\neping your personal chart and notes updated on your progress.</div>=0A<div =\r\nclass=3D\"clearl\">&nbsp;</div>=0A<div class=3D\"clearp\">&nbsp;</div><span cla=\r\nss=3D'collapseomatic ' id=3D'id2037'  title=3D\"Am I Always Going To Be With=\r\n The Same Trainer?\">Am I Always Going To Be With The Same Trainer?</span>=\r\n=0A<div id=3D'target-id2037' class=3D'collapseomatic_content '> Ideally, ye=\r\ns. This one-on-one training relationship will be helpful as you and your in=\r\nstructor work on your fitness goals by continually adjusting your workouts =\r\nand monitoring your progress. However, should your schedule conflict with y=\r\nour trainer&#8217;s, we will be happy to accommodate your needs.</div>=0A<d=\r\niv class=3D\"clearl\">&nbsp;</div>=0A<div class=3D\"clearp\">&nbsp;</div><span =\r\nclass=3D'collapseomatic ' id=3D'id6035'  title=3D\"Plan For 20 Minutes - Rea=\r\nlly?\">Plan For 20 Minutes - Really?</span>=0A<div id=3D'target-id6035' clas=\r\ns=3D'collapseomatic_content '> Yes, that is true, the exercise regime will =\r\ntake approximately 20-30 minutes, but give yourself enough time to get comf=\r\nortable and ready to work with your trainer. If you want to learn more abou=\r\nt why it only takes 20 minutes, please visit our <a href=3D\"http://informfi=\r\ntness.com/workout/how-it-works/\">How It Works</a> page for a more detailed =\r\nexplanation.</div>=0A<div class=3D\"clearl\">&nbsp;</div>=0A<div class=3D\"cle=\r\narp\">&nbsp;</div><span class=3D'collapseomatic ' id=3D'id2807'  title=3D\"Wh=\r\nat Amenities Are Provided?\">What Amenities Are Provided?</span>=0A<div id=\r\n=3D'target-id2807' class=3D'collapseomatic_content '> Most InForm Fitness f=\r\nacilities offer dressing rooms, lockers and showers for our clients=E2=80=\r\n=99 convenience. Exact amenities may vary with each location.<br />=0A</div>=\r\n=0A<div class=3D\"clearl\">&nbsp;</div>=0A<div class=3D\"clearp\">&nbsp;</div><=\r\nspan class=3D'collapseomatic ' id=3D'id3610'  title=3D\"What Can I Expect In=\r\n Each Workout?\">What Can I Expect In Each Workout?</span>=0A<div id=3D'targ=\r\net-id3610' class=3D'collapseomatic_content '> Your trainer will guide you t=\r\nhrough six to seven different strength-training exercises that will give yo=\r\nu an intense full-body workout.</div>=0A<div class=3D\"clearl\">&nbsp;</div>=\r\n=0A<div class=3D\"clearp\">&nbsp;</div><span class=3D'collapseomatic ' id=3D'=\r\nid8153'  title=3D\"What Should I Eat Before A Workout?\">What Should I Eat Be=\r\nfore A Workout?</span>=0A<div id=3D'target-id8153' class=3D'collapseomatic_=\r\ncontent '> This is actually one of the times when some carbs would be good =\r\nfor you =E2=80=93 because they provide the quick energy you need when you=\r\n=E2=80=99re on the go or about to work out. If you=E2=80=99re on your way t=\r\no the gym and your stomach is growling, eat an apple or orange. You=E2=80=\r\n=99ll get a boost from the fruit=E2=80=99s natural sugar and your body will=\r\n thank you. But, PLEASE, don=E2=80=99t eat a bagel and send your blood suga=\r\nr through the roof. Do yourself a favor and stick with natural and real who=\r\nle-energy sources.=C2=A0</div>=0A<div class=3D\"clearl\">&nbsp;</div>=0A<div =\r\nclass=3D\"clearp\">&nbsp;</div><span class=3D'collapseomatic ' id=3D'id5558' =\r\n title=3D\"What Are Your Hours?\">What Are Your Hours?</span>=0A<div id=3D'ta=\r\nrget-id5558' class=3D'collapseomatic_content '> We are open Monday-Friday f=\r\nrom 6 am to 8 pm and Saturday from 7 am to 3 pm.</div>=0A<div class=3D\"clea=\r\nrl\">&nbsp;</div>=0A<div class=3D\"clearp\">&nbsp;</div><span class=3D'collaps=\r\neomatic ' id=3D'id7104'  title=3D\"Where Are You Located?\">Where Are You Loc=\r\nated?</span>=0A<div id=3D'target-id7104' class=3D'collapseomatic_content '>=\r\n Our flagship InForm Fitness studio is located at 201 E 56th St., 2nd Floor=\r\n, just off the corner of 3rd Ave, in New York City. <!-- end of Header -->=0D=0A        =0D=0A=0D=0A        <!-- end =\r\nof slideshow -->=0D=0A        =0D=0A        <span class=3D\"clear\">&nbsp;</s=\r\npan>=0D=0A        <section id=3D\"maincontents\">=0D=0A        =0D=0A        =\r\n    <section id=3D\"contents\" class=3D\"grid_8\" style=3D\"padding-top:20px;\">=\r\n=0D=0A            \t<div id=3D\"page\">=0D=0A        \t\t                    <di=\r\nv id=3D\"breadcrumbs\">=0D=0A                        <!-- Breadcrumb NavXT 4.=\r\n1.0 -->=0A<span id=3D\"bstart\" style=3D\"color:#666666;font-weight:bold;\">You=\r\n are here:</span> <a style=3D\"color:#666666;\" title=3D\"Go to Home.\" href=3D=\r\n\"http://informfitness.com\">Home</a> &gt; <a style=3D\"color:#666666;\" title=\r\n=3D\"Go to Resources.\" href=3D\"http://informfitness.com/resources/\">Resource=\r\ns</a> &gt; Did You Know                    </div>                \t=0D=0A   =\r\n             \t<h2>Did You Know </h2>=0D=0A                    <p>Of the app=\r\nroximately 600 muscles in the human body, our tongue is the only one that i=\r\ns attached at only one end.</p>=0A<p><center><br />=0A<img src=3D\"http://in=\r\nformfitness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/divider4.png\" alt=3D\"\" /><br />=\r\n=0A</center></p>=0A<p>When we burn fat as our primary fuel source (optimize=\r\nd by a low carb diet), waste products build up and need to be eliminated fr=\r\nom our body. If you are well hydrated, these waste products are easily elim=\r\ninated by our kidneys, while our liver happily burns fat. Chronic dehydrati=\r\non, however, shifts the burden of eliminating the waste products to the liv=\r\ner thus impeding its role for burning fat.<br />=0ARecommendation &#8211; D=\r\nrink 2-3 liters of non-carbonated water a day.</p>=0A<p><center><br />=0A<i=\r\nmg src=3D\"http://informfitness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/divider4.png\"=\r\n alt=3D\"\" /></center></p>=0A<p>Treatments for obesity-related conditions su=\r\nch as diabetes, chronic joint pain, asthma, heart disease, and several type=\r\ns of cancer account for an estimated $147 billion annually, or roughly 10 p=\r\nercent of the nation&#8217;s total health care outlay. That&#8217;s 50 perc=\r\nent more than the cost of smoking-related treatments.</p>=0A<p><center><br =\r\n/>=0A<img src=3D\"http://informfitness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/divide=\r\nr4.png\" alt=3D\"\" /><br />=0A</center></p>=0A<p>Contrary to popular belief, =\r\nstrength training does NOT build new muscle cells. A muscle gets stronger w=\r\nhen the existing fibers become thicker, enabling it to generate more contra=\r\nctile force.</p>=0A<p><center><br />=0A<img src=3D\"http://informfitness.com=\r\n/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/divider4.png\" alt=3D\"\" /><br />=0A</center><br =\r\n/>=0AThe word &#8216;gymnasium&#8217;, aka gym, comes from the Greek word &=\r\n#8216;gymnos&#8217; meaning naked. In Ancient Greece, athletes competed in =\r\nthe nude to encourage aesthetic appreciation of the male body and as a trib=\r\nute to the gods.</p>=0A<p><center><br />=0A<img src=3D\"http://informfitness=\r\n.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/divider4.png\" alt=3D\"\" /><br />=0A</center>=\r\n</p>=0A<p>Legendary trainer and inventor, Arthur Jones once said, &#8220;If=\r\n the population as a whole would stop exercising, the general health of tha=\r\nt population would rise&#8221;. The point being that most people&#8217;s ex=\r\nercise programs do more harm than good.</p>=0A<p><center><br />=0A<img src=\r\n=3D\"http://informfitness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/divider4.png\" alt=\r\n=3D\"\" /><br />=0A</center></p>=0A<p>Avocados have more protein, potassium, =\r\nmagnesium, folic acid, vitamin E and fiber content per ounce than any other=\r\n fruit. They are cholesterol free AND are the closest food nutritionally to=\r\n breast milk!</p>=0A<p><center><br />=0A<img src=3D\"http://informfitness.co=\r\nm/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/divider4.png\" alt=3D\"\" /><br />=0A</center></p>=\r\n=0A<p>Sarcopenia =E2=80=93 or age related muscle loss =E2=80=93 begins to r=\r\napidly increase around the age of 40. Consequently, our metabolism slows, o=\r\nur bodies burn fewer calories, and we gain more fat. Strength training is t=\r\nhe ideal way to build or keep muscle as we age.</p>=0A<p><center><br />=0A<=\r\nimg src=3D\"http://informfitness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/divider4.png=\r\n\" alt=3D\"\" /><br />=0A</center></p>=0A<p>Longest muscle =E2=80=93 Sartorius=\r\n (stretches from the pelvis to the knee)<br />=0ALargest muscle (by mass) =\r\n=E2=80=93 Gluteus Maximus (butt)<br />=0ALargest muscle (by surface area) =\r\n=E2=80=93 Latissimus Dorsi (back muscle)<br />=0ASmallest muscle =E2=80=93 =\r\nStapedius (inner ear muscle)<br />=0AStrongest muscle =E2=80=93 (in terms o=\r\nf force applied per unit area) the Masseter or Jaw muscle</p>=0A<p><center>=\r\n<br />=0A<img src=3D\"http://informfitness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/di=\r\nvider4.png\" alt=3D\"\" /><br />=0A</center></p>=0A<p>Spot reduction is the fa=\r\nlse idea that if you exercise a specific muscle group you will decrease the=\r\n amount of fat in that area. In actuality, fat is stored and burned in patt=\r\nerns that are genetically determined.</p>=0A<p><center><br />=0A<img src=3D=\r\n\"http://informfitness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/divider4.png\" alt=3D\"\"=\r\n /><br />=0A</center></p>=0A<p>Unless you strength train and build muscle w=\r\nhile dieting, the body will instinctively cannibalize its muscle stores as =\r\ncompensation for the reduction in calories. As a result, your progression o=\r\nf fat loss will be much slower.</p>=0A<p><center><br />=0A<img src=3D\"http:=\r\n//informfitness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/divider4.png\" alt=3D\"\" /><br=\r\n />=0A</center></p>=0A<p>Muscle fibers fatigue sequentially, from slow twit=\r\nch to fast twitch, as the intensity increases. It&#8217;s the intensity of =\r\nthe exercise, not the speed of movement, which determines the muscle-fiber =\r\ninvolvement.</p>=0A<p><center><br />=0A<img src=3D\"http://informfitness.com=\r\n/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/divider4.png\" alt=3D\"\" /><br />=0A</center></p>=\r\n=0A<p>In 1971 Arthur Jones, the father of High-Intensity Training, helped C=\r\nasey Viator win the Mr. America competition. Casey would frequently train f=\r\nor just 25 minutes only 6 times a month.</p>=0A<p><center><br />=0A<img src=\r\n=3D\"http://informfitness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/divider4.png\" alt=\r\n=3D\"\" /><br />=0A</center></p>=0A<p>One of the liver&#8217;s primary functi=\r\nons is to metabolize fat for energy. If you are dehydrated, however, the li=\r\nver becomes overburdened with new responsibilities compromising its ability=\r\n to breakdown fatty acids. Moral: Stay hydrated, burn more fat.</p>=0A<p><c=\r\nenter><br />=0A<img src=3D\"http://informfitness.com/wp-content/uploads/2012=\r\n/06/divider4.png\" alt=3D\"\" /><br />=0A</center></p>=0A<p>From the start of =\r\nadulthood the length of our muscles is established and cannot change. No sp=\r\necific activity can elongate muscles=E2=80=A6for that to happen the length =\r\nof our bones would have to increase.</p>=0A<p>&nbsp;</p>=0A\t\t\t\t   =0D=0A   =\r\n             </div>=0D=0A                =0D=0A                =0D=0A      =\r\n          <span class=3D\"clear\">&nbsp;</span> =0D=0A                <!-- ma=\r\nin contents ends -->=0D=0A            </section>\t=0D=0A id=3D\"maincontents\">=0D=0A        =0D=0A            <section id=\r\n=3D\"contents\" class=3D\"grid_8\" style=3D\"padding-top:20px;\">=0D=0A          =\r\n  \t<div id=3D\"page\">=0D=0A        \t\t                    <div id=3D\"breadcru=\r\nmbs\">=0D=0A                        <!-- Breadcrumb NavXT 4.1.0 -->=0A<span =\r\nid=3D\"bstart\" style=3D\"color:#666666;font-weight:bold;\">You are here:</span=\r\n> <a style=3D\"color:#666666;\" title=3D\"Go to Home.\" href=3D\"http://informfi=\r\ntness.com\">Home</a> &gt; <a style=3D\"color:#666666;\" title=3D\"Go to Resourc=\r\nes.\" href=3D\"http://informfitness.com/resources/\">Resources</a> &gt; Eating=\r\n Healthy                    </div>                \t=0D=0A                \t<=\r\nh2>Eating Healthy </h2>=0D=0A                    <p>We don&#8217;t recommen=\r\nd dieting. Whoa &#8211; don&#8217;t run for the ice cream and cookies just =\r\nyet! We do recommend a healthy diet as one of the three pillars of =C2=A0lo=\r\nsing weight and achieving a healthy lifestyle.</p>=0A<h3>Aside from a low-c=\r\narb diet and exercise, how else can I lose my fat?</h3>=0A<p>1. <strong>Eat=\r\n when you=E2=80=99re hungry.=C2=A0</strong>Starving yourself just isn=E2=80=\r\n=99t sustainable. When you feel hunger pangs, eat! Just make smart choices.=\r\n</p>=0A<p>2. <strong>Stop eating when you=E2=80=99re full.=C2=A0</strong>Ho=\r\nw often do you still shovel the food in, even though you are no longer hung=\r\nry? Some of us are just so driven to complete a task that we go for a clean=\r\n plate for our signal to stop eating. Or, maybe you were raised with the gu=\r\nilt driven instructions from a parent encouraging you to finish everything =\r\non your plate and be grateful because there are so many children starving s=\r\nomewhere. But now you are a grown up and we encourage you to stop and think=\r\n before you take that second helping of chili, and ask yourself: are you st=\r\nill truly hungry, or are you just on autopilot?</p>=0A<p>3.<strong> Eat thi=\r\nngs you enjoy (but, again, within reason).=C2=A0</strong>If you don=E2=80=\r\n=99t like peas or broccoli, don=E2=80=99t eat them! Plenty of other nourish=\r\ning foods will keep you satisfied and happy. Eating should be a pleasure, n=\r\not a punishment.</p>=0A<p>4. <strong>Eat with awareness and sensitivity.=C2=\r\n=A0</strong>Try to view eating well as a central part of your healthy and h=\r\nappy life, and not as some chore. You=E2=80=99re more likely to stick to a =\r\nhealthy diet, and lose and keep fat off, if good food becomes an integral, =\r\nsavored, and positive aspect of your life.</p>=0A<p>We encourage you to lea=\r\nrn more about eating healthy and we&#8217;ve provided you with a <a href=3D=\r\n\"http://informfitness.com/resources/nutritional-guide/\">Nutritional Guide</=\r\na> that might help you make InFormed choices.</p>=0A\t\t\t\t   =0D=0A          =\r\n      </div>=0D=0A                =0D=0A                =0D=0A             =\r\n   <span class=3D\"clear\">&nbsp;</span> =0D=0A href=3D\"http://informfitness.c=\r\nom/resources/nutritional-guide/\">Nutritional Guide</a></li>=0A\t<li id=3D\"me=\r\nnu-item-847\" class=3D\"menu-item menu-item-type-post_type
